#: ../source/changeStreams.txt:9
msgid "Change Streams"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/changeStreams.txt:21
msgid ""
"Change streams allow applications to access real-time data changes "
"without the complexity and risk of tailing the :term:`oplog`. "
"Applications can use change streams to subscribe to all data changes on a"
" collection and immediately react to them."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/changeStreams.txt:28
msgid ""
"Change stream is only available if :readconcern:`\"majority\"` read "
"concern support is enabled (default)."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/changeStreams.txt:32
msgid "Open A Change Stream"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/changeStreams.txt:34
msgid ""
"You can only open a change stream against :doc:`replica sets "
"<replication>` or :doc:`sharded clusters </sharding>`. For a sharded "
"cluster, you must issue the open change stream operation against the "
":binary:`~bin.mongos`."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/changeStreams.txt:39
msgid ""
"The replica set or the sharded cluster must use replica set protocol "
"version 1 (:rsconf:`pv1 <protocolVersion>`) and :ref:`WiredTiger "
"<storage-wiredtiger>` storage engine (can be :ref:`encrypted <encrypted-"
"storage-engine>`)."
msgstr ""

